git config --global user.name "username" ->this set a global user for this pc
git config --global user.email "email" ->this set a global email for this pc

git init to initialize empty git repo in the present location
to deploy a page with github the main page name must be index.html
too stage a file to commit latter git add "file name" will stage the specific file,
if you want to stage all the files use git add '.' 

stage area "Staging area is files that are going to be a part of the next commit, which lets git know what changes in the file are going to occur for the next commit. The repository contains all of a project's commits."

to unStage use git rm --cached "file name"

to know the status of current working area use git status

to commit use git commit -m "massage" ->this massage will be shown to other dev to make them understand what changes you have done

<-to deploy->
to deploy a page with github the main page name must be index.html

go to the repository in github and go to setting and go down to github pages and click the link
then save the origin to master and save,then wait for 20sec then it will be deployed






